description: {"blocks":[{"key":"f294a","text":"This protocol describes sectioning for fresh frozen tissues for multimodal imaging including Hematoxylin \u0026 Eosin staining, DESI imaging mass spectrometry, SIMS imaging mass spectrometry and RNAscope imaging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

groups.title: Human BioMolecular Atlas Program (HuBMAP) Method Development Community

guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"3fcpo","text":"Upon finishing cryosectioning, remove the blade and dispose in sharps container before cleaning the cryostat.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7hr5e","text":"Discard tissue remnants in biohazard bag.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
materials_text: {"blocks":[{"key":"5n0nb","text":"Cryostat, Leica- CM 3050S","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"17p5h","text":"Accu-Edge Microtome Blades, Sakura- 4689","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d16hb","text":"Anti roll glass, Leica 14047742497","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"1ddpn","text":"Place the tissue block inside the cryostat at -20°C for 30 mins for equilibration. Also, place the slides and substrates inside the cryostat for cooling.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6tdvr","text":"Mount the tissue block on the chuck using water (no OCT) and adjust the angle of the chuck as needed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f3j19","text":"Trim the tissue block at 30-50µm thickness to obtain a flat surface.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d18kb","text":"Position the anti-roll bar appropriately so that it doesn’t scrape the tissue (if placed too far) or roll off of the block (if placed too near).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dtapd","text":"Clean the cryostat surface, anti-roll blade and forceps with ethanol before sectioning.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d0944","text":"Gently section the tissue at 8µm thickness using an anti-roll bar and place the consecutive sections on individual substrates. Adjust and flatten with a fine tipped brush if necessary. For H\u0026E, DESI and RNAscope imaging, tissue sections are placed on regular or positively charged microscope slides and on gold coated 2.5cm2 substrate for SIMS-imaging.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":323,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"eo9g","text":"Thaw mount the sections on the target using heat from the finger under the slide.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3gh1k","text":"Set the chamber temperature of the cryostat to -20C and object temperature to -18C to -20C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"516eo","text":"Place the blade in place and lock it.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
